hp?album=7&lang=english Pictures taken from Smolyan, Bulgaria]\n* [http://video.google.com/videoplay?docid=8795161973354047457&pl=true NASA video of eclipse]\n* [http://www.nasamike.com/main/eclipse/ Solar eclipse images and videos from Libya by traveling NASA employees and scientists]\n* [http://cmhas.wikispaces.com/EclipseLibyaTurkey Images by Crayford Manor House Astronomical Society from Libya and Turkey]\n* [http://www.spaceweather.com/eclipses/gallery_29mar06.htm Spaceweather.com Eclipse gallery]\n* [http://antwrp.gsfc.nasa.gov/apod/ap060330.html Antwrp.gsfc.nasa.gov] [[APOD]], 3/30/2006, When Diamonds Aren't Forever, totality from Greek island of Kastelorizo in the eastern Aegean\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20101119183820/http://antwrp.gsfc.nasa.gov/apod/ap060404.html Antwrp.gsfc.nasa.gov] [[APOD]], 4/4/2006, A Total Solar Eclipse over Turkey, totality from [[Adrasan, Kumluca]], [[Antalya Province]], Turkey\n* [http://antwrp.gsfc.nasa.gov/apod/ap060407.html Antwrp.gsfc.nasa.gov] [[APOD]], 4/7/2006, totality from [[Side, Turkey|Side]], Turkey, a larger version of the same picture chosen as APOD again on 7/26/2009, [http://antwrp.gsfc.nasa.gov/apod/ap090726.html The Big Corona], [http://www.koenvangorp.be/events/eclipse_2006.html Koenvangorp.be]\n* [http://antwrp.gsfc.nasa.gov/apod/ap060408.html Antwrp.gsfc.nasa.gov] [[APOD]], 4/8/2006, Vanishing Umbra, from [[Mount Hasan]] southeast of [[\u0130ncesu, Aksaray]], Turkey\n* [http://www.krysstal.com/ec2006.html The 2006 Eclipse in Turkey]\n* [http://www.izmiran.ru/info/personalia/molodensky/Eclips06.html Russian scientist observed eclipse]\n* [https://archive.is/20060405115220/http://solar-eclipse.uoa.gr/english/ University of Athens \u2013 Solar Eclipse 29/3/2006, Solar Party]\n* [http://www.eclipse2006.boun.edu.tr/eclipse_2006eng.html Solar Total Eclipse of 2006 March 29]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20061001175754/http://www.tug.tubitak.gov.tr/tutulma/english/main.html Tubitak.gov.tr], 29 March 2006 Tota